usage: build-lustre <builddir> <version>

Ex.

./build-lustre /dev/shm 2.10.8

It will install the required packages to build, so don't run it where you cannot
allow package installation.

When done the rpm packages will be locacated here <builddir>/*.rpm.

For a minimum install you need to install,

kmod-lustre-client
lustre-client

packages. 

